rder-left: 6px solid #f4f4f4; border-bottom: 2px solid transparent; transform: translateX(16px) translateY(-4px) rotate(30deg)\"></div></div><div style=\"margin-left: auto;\"> <div style=\" width: 0px; border-top: 8px solid #F4F4F4; border-right: 8px solid transparent; transform: translateY(16px);\"></div> <div style=\" background-color: #F4F4F4; flex-grow: 0; height: 12px; width: 16px; transform: translateY(-4px);\"></div> <div style=\" width: 0; height: 0; border-top: 8px solid #F4F4F4; border-left: 8px solid transparent; transform: translateY(-4px) translateX(8px);\"></div></div></div></a> <p style=\" margin:8px 0 0 0; padding:0 4px;\"> <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/p/BradVOjgiYk/?utm_source=ig_embed&amp;utm_campaign=loading\" style=\" color:#000; font-family:Arial,sans-serif; font-size:14px; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; line-height:17px; text-decoration:none; word-wrap:break-word;\" target=\"_blank\">Day THREE of Week 2 at #COP24 ‚Å£ ‚Å£ Amidst the flurry of activities at Katowice, it was comforting to have spotted familiar faces and to have recognised the voices of people just like me. Together with other Singaporean observers at COP24, I had the privilege of meeting Minister Masagos and members of the delegation for an informal discussion about Singapore‚Äôs challenges and efforts in tackling environmental issues. ‚Å£ ‚Å£ We spoke of plastics and waste, of recycling and energy, and of the need to change mindsets with interdisciplinary education. ‚Å£ ‚Å£ No doubt it was a short meeting. Yet today, I am reminded that not everything boils down to the overwhelming and sometimes alienating plane of international negotiations (important as they may be). Instead, we need to take these decisions back to our local communities and work to influence, inspire, and stir up sustainable change from the ground up. ‚Å£ ‚Å£ Above all, I left the meeting with a sense of reassurance, knowing that we are not alone in the fight towards climate action; we have each other to count on. My heart is full üá∏üá¨‚Å£ ‚Å£ &#8211; Wesley ü•¶</a></p> <p style=\" color:#c9c8cd; font-family:Arial,sans-serif; font-size:14px; line-height:17px; margin-bottom:0; margin-top:8px; overflow:hidden; padding:8px 0 7px; text-align:center; text-overflow:ellipsis; white-space:nowrap;\">A post shared by <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/pandasonthego/?utm_source=ig_embed&amp;utm_campaign=loading\" style=\" color:#c9c8cd; font-family:Arial,sans-serif; font-size:14px; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; line-height:17px;\" target=\"_blank\"> üêº Young Pandas of @wwfsg</a> (@pandasonthego) on <time style=\" font-family:Arial,sans-serif; font-size:14px; line-height:17px;\" datetime=\"2018-12-15T15:42:45+00:00\">Dec 15, 2018 at 7:42am PST</time></p></div></blockquote><script async src=\"//www.instagram.com/embed.js\"></script>\n</div></figure>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\"><strong>So, what is next (after education)?</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Education may be effective in changing the minds of Singaporeans when allowed to run its course, but this will take time ‚Äî possibly an entire generation‚Äôs worth. &nbsp;In the interim, there must be complementary measures put in place to stir climate action. These could include outreach activities and incentives to <a href=\"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/climate-change/2017/03/earth-hour-water-challenge/\">reduce our carbon footprint incurred from day to day living</a> (reducing electricity and water use, waste creation and disposal etc.).</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\"><strong>Be proud your own sustainability journey (and appreciate someone else&#8217;s)¬†¬†</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>There is also the subsequent question of how best to bridge the gap between head knowledge and actual action. We need to remember that changes towards sustainability do not have to be all-or-nothing. For instance, choosing to <a href=\"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/sustainable-consumption/2018/10/how-planet-friendly-is-your-favourite-hawker-food/\">consume less meat</a> more frequently throughout the week is not only environmentally sustainable, but is also healthier and more cost-effective. As such, the metric used to evaluate the success of environmental education should not be assessing uncompromising factors such as veganism uptake. Instead, it needs to appreciate how everyone‚Äôs journey towards increased environmental consciousness is unique and based on their personal circumstances. In doing so, people will be more likely to try knowing that is it not a false choice between being sustainable in every way and not caring about the environment.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\"><strong>Sacrifice goes a long, long way&nbsp;</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Finally (and perhaps the most difficult part of all), us Singaporeans need to recognise that moving towards and <a href=\"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/sustainable-consumption/2018/04/are-singaporeans-too-detached-to-care-about-plastic-waste/\">adopting an environmentally friendly lifestyle</a> will involve a sacrifice of sorts, whether that be financial resources or the luxury of convenience and time. These costs can only be absorbed by other parties to some extent and so the question for us all is how far we are willing to go out of way to save the environment for ourselves and for our children. I like to see the whole saga over tray deposits in hawker centres together with the <a href=\"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/ocean/2018/11/plastic-pollution-opinion-businesses-pact/\">possible ban on plastic bags in supermarkets</a> as illustrations of how initiating change is all about balancing our aspirations while ensuring that the process does not overly-burden our way of life, especially for those who are more vulnerable. Perhaps we still have a long way to go, but I am optimistic that we will get there eventually.<br></p>\n\n\n\n<p>With all that said, I leave you with my parting plea:<br></p>\n\n\n\n<p>The next time you hear someone tell you that the solution to climate change is education, please do not shy away from asking them to clarify what exactly they mean by that. Be bold in challenging their assumptions and asking for specifics when it comes to how education is supposed to fight climate change. More importantly, actively educate yourself and those around you ‚Äì be informed, because knowledge is power!</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em>Follow us and see more of Wesley&#8217;s updates from COP24 on </em><a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/pandasonthego/?hl=en\"><em>@pandasonthego</em></a><em>.</em></p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong><em>Read more about the </em></strong><a href=\"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/climate-change/2016/09/reality-of-climate-change-in-philippines/\"><strong><em>reality of climate change in Philippines</em></strong></a><strong><em>, our op-ed </em></strong><a href=\"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/sustainable-consumption/2018/04/plastics-enough-trash-talk/\"><strong><em>&#8216;Plastics: Enough Trash Talk&#8217;</em></strong></a><strong><em>, and the </em></strong><a href=\"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/wildlife/2018/08/the-inside-scoop-on-ivory-lane/\"><strong><em>inside scoop of our Ivory Lane campaign</em></strong></a><strong><em>.&nbsp;<br></em></strong><br></p>\n","uri":"what-is-climate-change-cop24-katowice-education/","author":{"name":null,"slug":null,"avatar":null},"featuredImage":{"altText":"what is climate change","srcSet":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Untitled-design-11.jpg 1000w, https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Untitled-design-11-300x225.jpg 300w"},"tags":{"nodes":[{"name":"Climate Change","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/climate-change/","slug":"climate-change"},{"name":"cop24","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/cop24/","slug":"cop24"},{"name":"environmental education","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/environmental-education/","slug":"environmental-education"},{"name":"katowice cop24 2018","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/tag/katowice-cop24-2018/","slug":"katowice-cop24-2018"}]},"categories":{"nodes":[{"name":"Climate Change","link":"https://dev-wwfsg.pantheonsite.io/category/climate-change/","slug":"climate-change"}]},"campaigns":{"nodes":[]}}}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"id":"cG9zdDozNDM5","uri":"what-is-climate-change-cop24-katowice-education/","title":"COP24: Why We Should Stop Saying the Solution to Climate Change is Education","databaseId":3439,"slug":"what-is-climate-change-cop24-katowice-education","excerpt":"<p>The writer is Panda Ambassador at WWF-Singapore, Wesley Poh, who was covering news from COP24 (2-15 Dec) at Katowice, Poland. Here, Wesley sheds light on why climate change is not as simple and straight-forward as you think it is.¬† KATOWICE, Poland, 13 Dec 2018 ‚Äî&nbsp; It is Education Day at COP24, and there are side [&hellip;]</p>\n","date":"2018-12-21T12:43:31"}}}